properties.areaDesc: Los Angeles County San Fernando Valley
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 3:56PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 25 to 35 mph with damaging gusts up to 60
mph.

* WHERE...San Fernando Valley.

* WHEN...From 8 PM Sunday to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down large objects such as
trees and power lines. Power outages are likely. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strongest winds Sunday night across
northern portions. Major roadways impacted by the strong winds
and potential damage include Interstates 5, 210, and 405, as
well as Highways 118, 134, and 170.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside around trees and branches. If
possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the
windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 8 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
